# Quality and Tooling

## Pre-commit / PR checklist

```bash
uv sync --all-packages
make lint-imports
make flct   # format + lint + mypy + import-linter + test
```

- Import-linter: 10 contracts in root `pyproject.toml`
- New package → update `[tool.uv.workspace]` members
- Cross-module import change → update `[[tool.importlinter.contracts]]`

## Makefile

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `make dev` | server + workers + flower + web |
| `make lint-imports` | module boundaries |
| `make flct` | full quality gate |
| `make k8s-build` | Docker images |

## Docker / K8s

- `SERVICE`: `cortex-server`, `sync-worker`, `ingestion-worker`, `flower`
- Do not use `cortex-worker` — removed
- Update `infra/docker/Dockerfile.python` when adding packages

## When changing architecture

- `docs/engineering/architecture/module-boundaries.md`
- `architecture.mmd`
- New ADR in `docs/engineering/decisions/` for significant decisions

## Minimal diff

- One PR = one domain concern when possible
- No unrelated refactors; no `.env` / credentials in git

